      • canExtract

        protected boolean canExtract(T extractedSimulated)
        Description copied from class: IngredientChannelAdapter
        Check if the given instance can be extracted. This is needed in cases where you want to block the extraction if it has not yet been indexed properly. Otherwise, changes to a storage may not be indexed at all, and important information may be lost.
        Overrides:
        canExtract in class IngredientChannelAdapter<T,M>
        Parameters:
        extractedSimulated - A simulated extraction.
        Returns:
        If the extraction is allowed.
